<item>
            <title>[MJAVADOC-149] Newline in ${project.organization.name} makes javadoc fail</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/MJAVADOC-149</link>
                <project id="12317529" key="MJAVADOC">Maven Javadoc Plugin (Moved to GitHub Issues)</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;Consider the following POM snippet:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;code panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;codeContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre class=&quot;code-java&quot;&gt;&amp;lt;organization&amp;gt;
    &amp;lt;name&amp;gt;
        My company,
        my department
    &amp;lt;/name&amp;gt;
&amp;lt;/organization&amp;gt;&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The Javadoc plugin outputs the following to the options file, using its default configuration:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;code panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;codeContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre class=&quot;code-java&quot;&gt;-bottom
&apos;Copyright &#169; 2007 My company,
      my department. All Rights Reserved.&apos;&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This actually makes javadoc fail with the following errors:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;code panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;codeContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre class=&quot;code-java&quot;&gt;javadoc: error - Illegal &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;package&lt;/span&gt; name: &lt;span class=&quot;code-quote&quot;&gt;&quot;department.&quot;&lt;/span&gt;
javadoc: error - Illegal &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;package&lt;/span&gt; name: &lt;span class=&quot;code-quote&quot;&gt;&quot;Reserved.&quot;&lt;/span&gt;
javadoc: error - Illegal &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;package&lt;/span&gt; name: &quot;&quot;
javadoc: warning - No source files &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;for&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;package&lt;/span&gt; my
javadoc: warning - No source files &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;for&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;package&lt;/span&gt; All
javadoc: warning - No source files &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;for&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;package&lt;/span&gt; Rights&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Since line terminators are used as separators within the arg files, the Javadoc plugin should replace line terminators (in all fashions) with spaces before writing out any POM value so that the formatting of the XML contents does not matter.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment>Maven 2.0.7, JDK 1.5.0_12, Win</environment>
